Arduino sketch to control an autonomous robot with a few sensors on board.

 - HMC6352 Compass
 - SR HC-04 Ultrasonic Sensor
 - DS18B20 1-wire temperature sensor
 - 2 x TB6612FNG motor drivers
 - MCP23017 I/O Extender
 
It's using a DFRobot Pirate 4WD Mobile Platform, wasn't sure if I could
run this off a single TB6612FNG so I went ahead and used 2 anyway. That's
why there's a MCP23017 in the mix too.

Requires:

1) Ruben Laguna's Arduino Library for Hmc6352
http://rubenlaguna.com/wp/2009/03/19/arduino-library-for-hmc6352/index.html/

2) Tim Eckel's NewPing Library
http://code.google.com/p/arduino-new-ping/

3) hacktronics Arduino 1-Wire Tutorial for DS18B20
http://www.hacktronics.com/Tutorials/arduino-1-wire-tutorial.html

4) bildr tutorial on the SparkFun TB6612FNG breakout
http://bildr.org/2012/04/tb6612fng-arduino/

5) John Boxall's tutorial on the MCP23017
http://tronixstuff.wordpress.com/2011/08/26/tutorial-maximising-your-arduinos-io-ports/

